<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="1552" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[178,1086,1070,1121]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552">Etymology: The name (Latin, adjective: skinny) refers to the slender habitus, one of the characters distinguishing this species from similar congeners.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="1553" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[178,1086,1136,1217]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552">
Description: Small and slender species, 
<quantity box="[703,788,1136,1158]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552" unit="mm" value="2.7">2.7 mm</quantity>
. Coloration: Head blackish; pronotum blackish-brown; elytra dark-brown; abdomen blackish, with the apex (segments VII-X) dark-brown. Legs and antennae yellowish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[178,1086,1232,1342]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552">
Head moderately transverse, approximately 1.15 times as broad as long; punctation conspicuously coarse and dense, only slightly sparser in posterior portion of dorsal surface (
<figureCitation box="[186,246,1291,1313]" captionStart="Figs 1-8" captionStartId="4.[178,218,1229,1249]" captionTargetBox="[179,1085,212,1212]" captionTargetId="figure-201@4.[178,1085,212,1218]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 1-8: Neosclerus macer nov.sp. (1-7) and N. schuelkei ASSING (8): (1) forebody; (2) male sternite VII; (3) male sternite VIII in ventral view; (4) anterior carinae of male sternite VIII in ventral view; (5) male sternite VIII in lateral view; (6, 8) aedeagus in lateral view; (7) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1: 0.5 mm; 2-3, 5: 0.2 mm; 4, 6-8: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5302506" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5302506/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
); interstices without microsculpture and glossy. Eyes large, but not reaching posterior margin of head; postocular portion short, but noticeable.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[178,1086,1357,1438]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552">
Pronotum approximately as long as broad and 0.85 times as wide as head; punctation as coarse and almost as dense as that of head (
<figureCitation box="[633,695,1387,1409]" captionStart="Figs 1-8" captionStartId="4.[178,218,1229,1249]" captionTargetBox="[179,1085,212,1212]" captionTargetId="figure-201@4.[178,1085,212,1218]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 1-8: Neosclerus macer nov.sp. (1-7) and N. schuelkei ASSING (8): (1) forebody; (2) male sternite VII; (3) male sternite VIII in ventral view; (4) anterior carinae of male sternite VIII in ventral view; (5) male sternite VIII in lateral view; (6, 8) aedeagus in lateral view; (7) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1: 0.5 mm; 2-3, 5: 0.2 mm; 4, 6-8: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5302506" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5302506/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
); midline narrowly impunctate; interstices without microsculpture and glossy.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[178,1086,1453,1563]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552">
Elytra approximately as long as pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[630,691,1453,1475]" captionStart="Figs 1-8" captionStartId="4.[178,218,1229,1249]" captionTargetBox="[179,1085,212,1212]" captionTargetId="figure-201@4.[178,1085,212,1218]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 1-8: Neosclerus macer nov.sp. (1-7) and N. schuelkei ASSING (8): (1) forebody; (2) male sternite VII; (3) male sternite VIII in ventral view; (4) anterior carinae of male sternite VIII in ventral view; (5) male sternite VIII in lateral view; (6, 8) aedeagus in lateral view; (7) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1: 0.5 mm; 2-3, 5: 0.2 mm; 4, 6-8: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5302506" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5302506/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
); punctation dense, defined, and relatively coarse, but distinctly less so than that of head and pronotum. Hind wings fully developed. Metatarsomere I longer than II, but shorter than the combined length of II and III.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5302506" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5302506" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5302506/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553" startId="4.[178,218,1229,1249]" targetBox="[179,1085,212,1212]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[178,1086,1229,1317]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[178,259,1229,1249]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">Figs 1-8</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="Assing, 2013" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2013" box="[274,441,1229,1249]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Neosclerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macer" status="nov.sp.">
<emphasis box="[274,441,1229,1249]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">Neosclerus macer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[451,518,1229,1249]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553" rank="species">nov.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<emphasis bold="true" box="[534,564,1229,1249]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">1-7</emphasis>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="ASSING" authorityName="ASSING" box="[624,819,1229,1249]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Neosclerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schuelkei">
<emphasis box="[624,739,1229,1249]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">N. schuelkei</emphasis>
ASSING
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis bold="true" box="[836,847,1229,1249]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">8</emphasis>
): (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[878,889,1229,1249]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">1</emphasis>
) forebody; (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1013,1024,1229,1249]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">2</emphasis>
) male sternite VII; (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[308,319,1252,1272]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">3</emphasis>
) male sternite VIII in ventral view; (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[679,690,1252,1272]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">4</emphasis>
) anterior carinae of male sternite VIII in ventral view; (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[313,324,1275,1295]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">5</emphasis>
) male sternite VIII in lateral view; (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[664,700,1275,1295]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">6, 8</emphasis>
) aedeagus in lateral view; (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[960,971,1275,1295]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">7</emphasis>
) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1: 0.5 mm; 2-3, 5: 0.2 mm; 4, 6-8: 0.1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="4.[178,1085,1332,1383]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">Abdomen distinctly narrower than elytra; posterior margin of tergite VII with palisade fringe.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[178,1086,1398,1537]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">
: sternite VII weakly oblong and with sparse pubescence, posterior margin with pair of small tooth-like processes (
<figureCitation box="[463,528,1428,1450]" captionStart="Figs 1-8" captionStartId="4.[178,218,1229,1249]" captionTargetBox="[179,1085,212,1212]" captionTargetId="figure-201@4.[178,1085,212,1218]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 1-8: Neosclerus macer nov.sp. (1-7) and N. schuelkei ASSING (8): (1) forebody; (2) male sternite VII; (3) male sternite VIII in ventral view; (4) anterior carinae of male sternite VIII in ventral view; (5) male sternite VIII in lateral view; (6, 8) aedeagus in lateral view; (7) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1: 0.5 mm; 2-3, 5: 0.2 mm; 4, 6-8: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5302506" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5302506/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
); sternite VIII oblong, anteriorly with pair of carinae posteriorly extending into a short process with a terminal seta, posterior excision moderately deep (
<figureCitation box="[297,386,1486,1508]" captionStart="Figs 1-8" captionStartId="4.[178,218,1229,1249]" captionTargetBox="[179,1085,212,1212]" captionTargetId="figure-201@4.[178,1085,212,1218]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 1-8: Neosclerus macer nov.sp. (1-7) and N. schuelkei ASSING (8): (1) forebody; (2) male sternite VII; (3) male sternite VIII in ventral view; (4) anterior carinae of male sternite VIII in ventral view; (5) male sternite VIII in lateral view; (6, 8) aedeagus in lateral view; (7) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1: 0.5 mm; 2-3, 5: 0.2 mm; 4, 6-8: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5302506" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5302506/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">Figs 3-5</figureCitation>
); aedeagus 
<quantity box="[508,599,1486,1508]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553" unit="mm" value="0.45">0.45 mm</quantity>
long, ventral process subapically bent and apically acute (
<figureCitation box="[301,388,1515,1537]" captionStart="Figs 1-8" captionStartId="4.[178,218,1229,1249]" captionTargetBox="[179,1085,212,1212]" captionTargetId="figure-201@4.[178,1085,212,1218]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 1-8: Neosclerus macer nov.sp. (1-7) and N. schuelkei ASSING (8): (1) forebody; (2) male sternite VII; (3) male sternite VIII in ventral view; (4) anterior carinae of male sternite VIII in ventral view; (5) male sternite VIII in lateral view; (6, 8) aedeagus in lateral view; (7) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1: 0.5 mm; 2-3, 5: 0.2 mm; 4, 6-8: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5302506" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5302506/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">Figs 6-7</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="1554" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[178,1086,1553,1604]" lastBlockId="5.[178,1086,218,533]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="1554" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">
Comparative notes: Based on the synapomorphically derived shapes of the male sternites VII (bidentate posterior margin) and VIII (anteriorly bicarinate), as well as on the similar general morphology of the aedeagus, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2013" box="[755,854,219,240]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Neosclerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macer">
<emphasis box="[755,854,219,240]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554">N. macer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is undoubtedly most closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="ASSING 2011" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2011" box="[364,656,248,270]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Neosclerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicarinatus">
<emphasis box="[364,511,248,270]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554">N. bicarinatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="ASSING V" box="[520,656,248,270]" journalOrPublisher="Beitrage zur Entomologie, Keltern" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554" pagination="89 - 148" part="61" refId="ref3466" refString="ASSING V. (2011 a): A revision of the genus Neosclerus CAMERON (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). - Beitrage zur Entomologie, Keltern 61 (1): 89 - 148." title="A revision of the genus Neosclerus CAMERON (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae)" type="journal article" year="2011">ASSING 2011</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[722,811,248,270]" name="Vietnam" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
, most likely its sister species. In the key in 
<bibRefCitation author="ASSING V" box="[365,528,277,299]" journalOrPublisher="Beitrage zur Entomologie, Keltern" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554" pagination="89 - 148" part="61" refId="ref3466" refString="ASSING V. (2011 a): A revision of the genus Neosclerus CAMERON (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). - Beitrage zur Entomologie, Keltern 61 (1): 89 - 148." title="A revision of the genus Neosclerus CAMERON (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae)" type="journal article" year="2011">ASSING (2011a)</bibRefCitation>
, the new species would key out at couplet 16, together with 
<taxonomicName authority="ASSING 2011" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2011" box="[234,481,306,328]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Neosclerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glaber">
<emphasis box="[234,333,306,328]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554">N. glaber</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="ASSING V" box="[344,481,306,328]" journalOrPublisher="Beitrage zur Entomologie, Keltern" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554" pagination="89 - 148" part="61" refId="ref3466" refString="ASSING V. (2011 a): A revision of the genus Neosclerus CAMERON (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). - Beitrage zur Entomologie, Keltern 61 (1): 89 - 148." title="A revision of the genus Neosclerus CAMERON (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae)" type="journal article" year="2011">ASSING 2011</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2011" box="[539,687,306,328]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Neosclerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicarinatus">
<emphasis box="[539,687,306,328]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554">N. bicarinatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is distinguished from both by the shape of the aedeagus, the more slender pronotum, and the distinctly coarser punctation of the elytra, from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2011" box="[376,474,365,387]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Neosclerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glaber">
<emphasis box="[376,474,365,387]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554">N. glaber</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
additionally by the modifications of the male sternites VII and VIII, and from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2011" box="[382,528,394,416]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Neosclerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicarinatus">
<emphasis box="[382,528,394,416]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554">N. bicarinatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the coarser and denser punctation of the head, the uniformly dark coloration of the elytra (
<taxonomicName authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2011" box="[611,760,423,445]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Neosclerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicarinatus">
<emphasis box="[611,760,423,445]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554">N. bicarinatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: humeral angles and posterior margin reddish), the more narrowly separated and differently shaped carinae on the male sternite VIII, as well as by the less pronounced posterior processes of the male sternite VII. For illustrations of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2011" box="[421,516,511,533]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Neosclerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glaber">
<emphasis box="[421,516,511,533]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554">N. glaber</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2011" box="[566,710,511,533]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Neosclerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicarinatus">
<emphasis box="[566,710,511,533]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554">N. bicarinatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
see 
<bibRefCitation author="ASSING V" box="[755,920,511,533]" journalOrPublisher="Beitrage zur Entomologie, Keltern" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554" pagination="89 - 148" part="61" refId="ref3466" refString="ASSING V. (2011 a): A revision of the genus Neosclerus CAMERON (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). - Beitrage zur Entomologie, Keltern 61 (1): 89 - 148." title="A revision of the genus Neosclerus CAMERON (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae)" type="journal article" year="2011">ASSING (2011a)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
