<quantity box="[780,862,578,600]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554" unit="m" value="1500.0">1500 m</quantity>
. The fully developed hind wings suggest that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2013" box="[422,515,608,629]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Neosclerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macer">
<emphasis box="[422,515,608,629]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554">N. macer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be widespread.
</paragraph>
